mary` — find last assistant text block\n\n## Step 2: Package Structure\n\nSince the binary has significant logic, organize into a package rather than one giant main.go:\n\n```\ncmd/entire-agent-cursor/\n├── main.go              # Entry point, subcommand dispatch\n├── cursor.go            # Core logic: detect, session management, path helpers\n├── hooks.go             # Hook install/uninstall/are-installed logic\n├── lifecycle.go         # ParseHookEvent: 7 hook parsers\n├── transcript.go        # TranscriptAnalyzer: position, prompts, summary, modified files\n└── types.go             # Hook input types, hooks.json types\n```\n\nAll files in `package main`.\n\n## Step 3: Reuse Shared Packages\n\nThe binary can import shared packages from this repo since it's in the same module:\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/agent` — `ChunkJSONL`, `ReassembleJSONL`, `HookInput`, `Event`, `EventType`, `AgentSession`\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/transcript` — `ParseFromFileAtLine`, `ParseFromBytes`, `ExtractUserContent`, type constants\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/textutil` — `StripIDEContextTags`\n- `github.com/entireio/cli/cmd/entire/cli/jsonutil` — `MarshalIndentWithNewline`\n\n**Key difference from built-in agent:** The binary communicates via JSON stdout, not Go interfaces. Each subcommand reads args/stdin, does the work, and outputs JSON to stdout.\n\n## Step 4: Protocol Response Details\n\n### `info` response (static):\n```json\n{\n  \"protocol_version\": 1,\n  \"name\": \"cursor\",\n  \"type\": \"Cursor\",\n  \"description\": \"Cursor - AI-powered code editor\",\n  \"is_preview\": true,\n  \"protected_dirs\": [\".cursor\"],\n  \"hook_names\": [\"session-start\",\"session-end\",\"before-submit-prompt\",\"stop\",\"pre-compact\",\"subagent-start\",\"subagent-stop\"],\n  \"capabilities\": {\n    \"hooks\": true,\n    \"transcript_analyzer\": true,\n    \"transcript_preparer\": false,\n    \"token_calculator\": false,\n    \"text_generator\": 